subject: p13762730
Findings: A dual-lead left pectoral pacemaker device has its leads terminating at expected locations in the right atrium and right ventricle. No pneumothorax. Bilateral pleural effusions and bibasal atelectases are mild. Bilateral lungs are remarkable for mild vascular and interstitial prominence, likely congestion. Normal heart size, mediastinal and hilar contours are unchanged in appearance since .
